Introduction¶

I'm going to showcase the data analysis steps on The Movies DB dataset , containing about 10 k movies and about 18 features for each, including several core features such as budget,revenue,genres,ratings,..etc

We can raise several quietions :

1st Group --> Popularity related questions:

  1. What are most popular movie genres through time?
  2. who are most popular directors in the last 10 years?

2nd Group --> Revenue related questions:

  1. What kinds of properties are associated with movies that have high revenues?
  2. How do revenue and budget correlate?
  3. Does series movies revenue increase/decrease for each new chapter?

  1. There are 5696 zero-budget records and 6016 zero-revenue records , means that more than half of data has zero budget/revenue values , it's not logic that all this portion represents indei(self-funded) movies
    Action :so,we would remove this zero-values when answering any revenue/budget related questions
  1. There are some clear outliers such as :A) in popularity column the 32.9 value is clearly out of range as almost 90% of values lies below 1. B)the runtime column has a value of 900 mins (15 hours !) sound a so clear outlier , but fter investigation, it was a 15-episode documentary about history of film which sounds a little bit wrongly found in this "Movies" dataset
    Action : for popularity related questions i will depend on the vote_avg column as it has clear scaling (10 degree scale raings) unlike the popularity column have diverse numbers with no clear scale or criteria.
  1. More than 50% of dataset's movies are within the last 10 years while it cover a span time of 55 years.
    Action : so it sounds logic to have some popularity related analytics over the last 10 years only.

Dataset info and header findings:

  1. Release date column type should be tranformed to date as it's an object "string"
  2. Most columns that have significant count of null values are the less important columns and to be trimmed such as : hompage , tagline, overview, keywords

def sep_top(df,col,n):
    
    """
    Takes a df column(col) with mulitple stick seprarated values
    and returns a list of unique top (n) frequent values
    """
    #will take a column, and separate the string by '|'
    data = df[col].str.cat(sep = '|')
    
    #get a pandas series storing separate values
    data = pd.Series(data.split('|'))
    
    #get unique to n frequent values
    data = data.value_counts()[:n].index.tolist()
                     
                     
    return data
In [13]:
def get_vote(data):
    
    """
    Takes a list of unique items
    gets the average voting per item in a sorted dataframe
    """
    #create a dic
    dict_df = {key:[] for key in data}
    #update dict with average voting for every genre(key)
    for word in data:
        vote = df[df.genres.str.contains(word)].vote_average.mean()
        dict_df[word].append(vote)
    #get the DF of the dict
    new_df = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(dict_df)
    new_df = new_df.T
    new_df.columns = ['avg_vote']
    new_df.sort_values(['avg_vote'],ascending = False, inplace = True)
    return new_df

Regarding above charts , it seems that there is no general Answer to our 5th and last question "Does series movies revenue increase/decrease for each new chapter?", but we can say that :¶

1. real-world action and avdentures movie are more liekly not only to preserve their revenue levels through series like MI series but also have increasing revenues for each new movie like fast&furoius .¶

2. Unlike super heroes and fantasy movies like "spider-man and superman" which have declining revenues after very high revenues for their 1st chapter¶

Conclusions¶

Popularity related questions:¶

  1. For the most popular Movie Genres , after working on nearly whole dataset whithout any filtters ,i used the vote_average to measure popularity instead of "popularity" column as it has no clear measure criteria or scale , it showed that drama comes first and crime as scond and the third was romance, this could lead us that people are mainly attracted by targeting their feelings and challenging their minds!
  1. For most popular directors , i have filter to the last 10 years(reduce count to 5.5k) to be more specific and have more meanningful resutls , then filtering on directors with more than 2 movies(count become 2 k) , to have a sensible & comparable average voting for every director , finding out C.Nolan on top which is a very logic result with his unique sense in film making also with his masterpiece "Interstellar" in 2014.

Revenue related questions:¶

for all revenue-based analysis , i have removed all zero-values in revenue and budget , which has reduced the count to !3.5k rows

  1. For properties associated with movies that have high revenues, the most clear features increasing with revenue is the average vote , as higher revenues has higher ratings , which is very reasonable, The more people attend the movie (higher revenue) reflects a positive feedback , yes correlation doesn't imply causation but the people attendance and popularity association is a rule of thumb confirmed by this analytics.
  1. For revenue and budget correlation , this is a little bit confusing , as there is no clear correlation between both , while i thought they should be correlated , but it's found that whithin budgets from 100M to 250M there is a direct correlation, while below 100M and above 250M budgets has no clear correlations.
  1. For series movies revenue increase/decrease , i have checked the revenue of 5 well-known movie series over time , i have found two trend : A) the 1st is for real-world action and adventures movies that their revenue still consistent over time for new parts (Mission Imposible) or even increasing by time (Fast&Furious). B)the 2nd is for super-heroes and fantasy movies that it starts with a very high revenue for 1st part and start to deline over time for new parts which could be interpreted that people are facinated by the 1st appearance of the hero and then they become no more excited as in the begining.

Limitaions:¶

  1. having more than half of the dataset with zero values in budget and revenue which should affect negatively on the quality of analysis related to revenue & budget

  2. having some issues values in the dataset like the values of movie-budget which has a typo, a few of this issues could affect the overall analysis

  3. i had to use the vote_average column to measure popularity as the "popularity" column given has no clear criteria of mesurement , so i coudln't depend on it
